OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1777914346
OL,3,CKing starts Bermuda visit with boat
OL,4,Ctrip, dancing and slavery exhibit
OL,6,FThe King was received by the
OL,7,FCommanding Officer of the Royal
OL,8,FBermuda Regiment, Lieutenant Colonel
OL,9,FDuncan Simons, with the moment watched
OL,10,Fby hundreds of school children and
OL,11,Fislanders.
OL,13,FMany of the islanders had come
OL,14,Fprepared for the royal visit, with one
OL,15,Flittle boy, Theo Godfrey, aged four,
OL,16,Fdressed like a guardsman in a red
OL,17,Ftunic and imitation bearskin hat.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1777914346
OL,3,CKing starts Bermuda visit with boat
OL,4,Ctrip, dancing and slavery exhibit
OL,6,FHis mother purchased the outfit from
OL,7,Fthe official Buckingham Palace shop
OL,8,Ftwo years ago and joked: "He's worn it
OL,9,Fever since!"
OL,11,FCharles stood on a dais as the royal
OL,12,Fsalute was given by the troops and
OL,13,Fremained motionless as the national
OL,14,Fanthem was played by a regimental band.
OL,16,FParade Commander, Major Kenji Bean,
OL,17,Fthen invited the King to inspect the
OL,18,Fguard of honour and he walked with
OL,19,FCharles as he strode past the troops.
OL,26,@qD@LO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
