OL,3,CKing starts Bermuda visit with boat
OL,4,Ctrip, dancing and slavery exhibit
OL,6,FCharles then travelled to Trunk
OL,7,Fisland, one of the many rocky outcrops
OL,8,Faround Bermuda, to chat to children
OL,9,Fbeing taught about conservation and
OL,10,Fwildlife through practical education,
OL,11,Fknown as living classrooms, led by the
OL,12,FBermuda Zoological Society (BZS).
OL,14,FThe King planted a cedar tree, a
OL,15,Fnative species that has been mostly
OL,16,Flost from the island and which
OL,17,Fprovided hurricane protection and
OL,18,Fother benefits.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1777914346
OL,3,CKing starts Bermuda visit with boat
OL,4,Ctrip, dancing and slavery exhibit
OL,6,FHe was also joined by a group of
OL,7,Fchildren as they watched three land
OL,8,Fhermit crabs being released and
OL,9,Fscuttling into the undergrowth after
OL,10,Fbeing moved from a development site
OL,11,Fthat threatened them.
OL,13,FAs well as being on land, the King
OL,14,Falso joined Bermuda's coastguard in a
OL,15,Fboat trip, where he learned about
OL,16,Ftheir work combatting illegal fishing
OL,17,Fand smuggling.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1777914346
OL,3,CKing starts Bermuda visit with boat
OL,4,Ctrip, dancing and slavery exhibit
OL,6,FHe also travelled to the National
OL,7,FMuseum of Bermuda, where he viewed a
OL,8,Fdisplay at the 1850 Ordnance House
OL,9,Fwhich traced darker moments in the
OL,10,Fisland's history, with a cabinet
OL,11,Fdedicated to trade, slavery and
OL,12,Fconquest.
OL,14,FIt included a drawn image of shackled
OL,15,Fmen sitting in a slave ship and
OL,16,Fseveral examples of neck irons.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1777914346
OL,3,CKing starts Bermuda visit with boat
OL,4,Ctrip, dancing and slavery exhibit
OL,6,FHe also watched a performance of the
OL,7,Fisland's Gombey dance tradition, an
OL,8,Fexpression of culture that had been
OL,9,Frestricted during slavery to just a
OL,10,Ffew times a year.
OL,12,FIrwin Trott, spokesman for the
OL,13,FBermudan Gombey dance troops, said
OL,14,Fafter meeting the King: "I told him
OL,15,Fthat it's a combination of cultures,
OL,16,FAfrican, Caribbean, West Indian,
OL,17,FNative American and, of course, Great
OL,18,FBritain.
OL,26,@vD@YOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31709
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1777914346
OL,3,CKing starts Bermuda visit with boat
OL,4,Ctrip, dancing and slavery exhibit
OL,6,F"Gombey is a premise from the Atlantic
OL,7,FSlave Trade when they were brought
OL,8,Fover by the colonisers and shipped to
OL,9,FNew England and the Caribbean islands.
OL,11,F"Even though they were stripped of
OL,12,Ftheir identity, names were taken,
OL,13,Ftheir language was taken, deep in
OL,14,Ftheir heart they maintained their
OL,15,Fculture, and so it still flourished
OL,16,Fthroughout the Caribbean.
OL,18,F"It was prohibited, so they were only
OL,19,Fpermitted to perform on Christmas and
OL,20,FNew Year's."
OL,26,@nD@AOUzD@AOU|D@LO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/12
